// Modified by Pilgrim Tabby, 2026, with notch calibration instructions

--- DEFAULT MODE ---

Hold start for ~8 seconds : Enters mapping mode

--- Mapping management mode ---

1) DPAD(any direction) -> Load mapping and exit

2) R -> Enters the R menu

3) START -> Exit

4) ZABXYL -> Code entry...


--- R menu ---

1) DPAD(any direction) -> Save mapping and exit

2) Z -> Toggle dead zone, save and exit

3) START -> Load default (standard) mapping and exit

4) L followed by DPAD (any direction) -> Make saved mapping active by defaut

5) L followed by START -> Make the built-in (standard) mapping active by default

6) B -> Cycle stick conversion mode (v1.5 style, v2.0 standard style [default], and extended style). Save and exit.

7) X -> Restore factory defaults

8) Y -> Notch calibration wizard. The LED blinks after each step.

  - Leave stick in neutral position and press A
  - Point stick up and press A
  - Point stick up-right and press A
  - Point stick right and press A
  - Point stick down-right and press A
  - Point stick down and press A
  - Point stick down-left and press A
  - Point stick left and press A
  - Point stick up-left and press A

9) A -> Remove saved notch calibration.
